import humanizer
text = """In previous discussions, the focus has been on clarifying the foundations of our knowledge concerning existence. The central question has been: what entities in the universe are known to us through direct acquaintance? The conclusion reached is that we are acquainted with our sense-data and, most likely, with ourselves. These constitute the immediate objects of knowledge whose existence we can affirm with certainty. In addition, past sense-data that we remember are also known to have existed. Together, these elements form the fundamental data upon which our knowledge is built. However, these data alone are insufficient for extending knowledge beyond immediate experience."""

print(humanizer.humanize(text))

